		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Hmm, I am not sure what level mobs you are looking at, so I suppose the pp would have to be good for the mob's level, or you can do quests to make money.<br>You could get a partner and try doing the EE's in Beholder, so that you can get optic nerves and do the crafted bracer quest (costs about 105 pp to do, you can get a return of 10-45pp per bracer if they sell), or maybe some other quests.&nbsp;&nbsp;Crag spiders can be rewarding for their silks and poison sacs (in EK), but once again, it's debatable how much they will pay off.  Sometimes they drop a lot, sometimes they drop nothing.  <br>  Something you can also try is being a bank machine in high level zones like SK or Rathe Mountains.  People drop their copper or trade it in at good rates, so you could make a few pp there.<br>  I understand that aviaks are very rich mobs, so you could try killing them&gt; They give you xp and and up to a few pp.<br>Lastly, you could try Area effect dd's and shower spells to kill many mobs at once that are levels below you, like gnolls in EK.  Killing 5 at once could mean a few pp.<br>At 22 it's hard to find good ways to make money.  You may have to accept being broke until you can tp at 29.<br>Good luck :)<br>BTW, If your wis is somewhere past 150, I wouldn't worry to much about upgrading.  I would just level, beacause soon the money will roll in, or you can get the items yourself.  Sorry I couldn't be of more help.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a>