		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Nov 14th 8:16 PM 2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=8&mid=9729235946024&num=6&post=1&replyto=97425096713178"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=97425096713178></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I'd like to try to give you a little assistance, based upon my own experience at this level (22 or so).&nbsp;&nbsp;First, I'd like to comment on the earlier posts, so you stay alive.  Capt Surestout in OOT is on the 2nd island west of Sisters, where the boat from Freeport to BB stops first.  The good Captain does drop the Bracers of Erollisi, which does sell for 25 pp or so, and it is lore, so you can only hold one at a time.  Problems are that the Captain is level 24-25 and will paste your solo ass at 22, as will the many level 40+ Seafury Cyclops that spawn on this island.  Also, you have to go sell after EVERY kill, assuming you can kill the Captain at 22 - you can't kite on that island very safely.  Also, high-level players camp this island, since the Ancient Cyclops who drops the ring for the Journeyman's Boots spawns here as well, and they often whack the Capt to relieve the boredom.  You may never see the Capt at all if there's an AC camp on.<br><br>The SK raider camp isn't a bad suggestion, but it is tedious - you'll have to pull and kill one raider at a time.  Since they're 11-12ish only one should come at a time.  If their bandit sashes are the same as the ones from the bandits in WK, you take them to Chesgard Sydwen (spelling) at the House of Thunder in Qeynos (maps at <a href="http://eqatlas.com" target=_new>http://eqatlas.com</a>).  Friend Chesgard gives a bronze weapon for each sash, and these weapons sell to the merchants for 1-3 plat each.  You can of course do the same thing at the bandit camp in West Karana (WK), at about loc neg 3700, neg 11,000.<br><br>If you'd like to get a little experience while you're at it, try the aviak guards in Lake Rathetear.  There are 2-3 sets of spawns, with 1, 2 or 3 spawns at each of several different sites.  These guys are good xp and loot for their level (18-22), dropping anywhere from a few gold to 2 plat each time.  You need a group to handle the multiple spawns at first, but a druid can handle the 2-spawn solo from 24-25 onward with levitate and harmony.<br><br>The Hermit in South Karana (SK) is another solo alternative around 22 - he is an unkempt druid at about level 20-23, spawn level varies, but he drops fine steel weapons, gold and plat in varying amounts.<br><br>Also in SK is the aviak city near the Lake Rathe zone - try pulling birds that con blue to you at 22 - some will be red, some yellow, some blue and some green, depending upon their type.  Avocets are 28-30, then harriers, rooks, other types, and egrets on the bottom in the high teens.  Beware egrets which can run with SoW speed unless snared.  Egrets and other will sometimes drop fine steel or bronze weapons, although seldom.<br><br>In my experience, Kunark mobs may be good experience, but not particularly good loot, Kunark zones are big, so it's difficult to get to a zone point for safety even with SoW, there are almost no druid rings for convenient travel, and there's one city for good race characters (i.e., we druids) on the whole damn continent.  On top of all that, every player and his brother is in Kunark, so the zones are overloaded, lag is prevalent, pathing is weird and mobs poof on you.  Stay away from Kunark, IMO.<br><br>What I'm leading up to is that loot drops  increase with mob level, and that your bank savings will rise with your level, or at least they have for me, and I was in your shoes only a couple levels ago.  Wisdom items are less common in the game than INT or even STR, so we have it a little tougher since a third of all characters are druids and demand is high.  Good luck.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhba